2
00:00:48,090 --> 00:00:51,301
[door opens and closes]

3
00:00:53,469 --> 00:00:56,390
Clara! Right on time.

4
00:00:56,472 --> 00:00:59,183
I know, Mom. I'm so sorry!
The roads are a mess.

5
00:00:59,393 --> 00:01:01,060
They always are this time of the year.

6
00:01:01,270 --> 00:01:03,521
- That's why I asked you to come early.
- [Clara] I know.

7
00:01:05,481 --> 00:01:07,525
- Wow! Mom!
- [Lydia] Hmm?

8
00:01:07,942 --> 00:01:09,861
- [Clara] This is so beautiful.
- [Lydia] Hmm.

9
00:01:11,362 --> 00:01:13,073
I think this is your best one ever.

10
00:01:13,531 --> 00:01:14,615
It has to be.

11
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:17,326
I'm being featured
in <i>Seasons Magazine </i>for Christmas.

12
00:01:17,411 --> 00:01:19,037
- You are?
- Mm-hmm.

13
00:01:19,412 --> 00:01:20,454
- Wow!
- [Lydia giggles]

14
00:01:20,539 --> 00:01:22,415
- I love these windows.
- [cell phone rings]

15
00:01:24,835 --> 00:01:26,795
- It's Bonnie.
- [Lydia] But of course.

16
00:01:27,462 --> 00:01:28,504
Hey, Bonnie.

17
00:01:29,131 --> 00:01:30,215
Yeah, Bonnie, slow down.

18
00:01:31,549 --> 00:01:34,093
Well, yeah, it's Christmas.
We always get slammed.

19
00:01:37,055 --> 00:01:37,930
Again?

20
00:01:40,016 --> 00:01:43,645
Yeah, sure. I'll be right in.

21
00:01:44,228 --> 00:01:45,688
- [sighs]
- [cell phone beeps]

22
00:01:47,481 --> 00:01:49,276
- Mom.
- Mm-hmm?

23
00:01:49,859 --> 00:01:51,694
I'm really sorry, but I have to go.

24
00:01:52,236 --> 00:01:54,489
You're really wasting
your talents there, sweetheart.

25
00:01:56,073 --> 00:01:57,742
Can we have a rain check
on baking those cookies?

26
00:01:57,825 --> 00:01:58,784
[Lydia] Oh, no!

27
00:01:58,868 --> 00:02:02,331
Your mother waits for no one,
first born or otherwise.

28
00:02:02,581 --> 00:02:04,540
How do you think your father
became so punctual?

29
00:02:04,915 --> 00:02:06,168
[both laugh]

30
00:02:07,376 --> 00:02:08,336
He was pretty punctual.

31
00:02:08,419 --> 00:02:10,004
- Mm-hmm.
- I love you.

32
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:12,633
- I love you too. Be careful.
- I will.

33
00:02:13,550 --> 00:02:16,010
- Bye.
- Bye.

34
00:02:17,387 --> 00:02:18,847
[door opens]

35
00:02:18,972 --> 00:02:20,139
[sighs]

36
00:02:20,264 --> 00:02:21,432
[door closes]

37
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:27,229
Right there. Yes, perfect.

38
00:02:29,066 --> 00:02:31,901
Welcome back
to <i>Can You Stand The Heat!</i>

39
00:02:32,235 --> 00:02:35,155
We started with 50 super celebrity chefs,

40
00:02:35,405 --> 00:02:38,491
and managed to whittle
it down to just three!

41
00:02:38,824 --> 00:02:41,286
So, who's it gonna be?

42
00:02:41,828 --> 00:02:42,996
- Mike Mahoney...
- [audience applauds]

43
00:02:43,079 --> 00:02:44,872
...whose big talent is second only

44
00:02:44,956 --> 00:02:46,082
- to his big mouth?
- Big Mike!

45
00:02:46,165 --> 00:02:47,417
What's that catchphrase?

46
00:02:47,626 --> 00:02:50,586
[all] Let's get cooking!

47
00:02:52,004 --> 00:02:55,300
Mike is in the house, baby!
That's right! Whoo!

48
00:02:56,259 --> 00:02:57,468
[TV hostess] Or Sharl Shaunnessy?

49
00:02:58,135 --> 00:03:01,431
The only baker who has what it takes
to rise to the top.

50
00:03:01,639 --> 00:03:04,558
Tortured artist of cakes
and pastries alike.

51
00:03:04,893 --> 00:03:06,895
[audience clapping and cheering]

52
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:14,360
[audience gasps]

53
00:03:14,443 --> 00:03:17,489
Or will it be Manhattan's
hottest celebrity chef,

54
00:03:17,697 --> 00:03:21,325
restaurateur and bachelor, Shane Roarke?

55
00:03:21,409 --> 00:03:25,704
- [clapping]
- [women cheering]

56
00:03:31,711 --> 00:03:34,798
[Shane chuckles] <i>Huh? Huh?</i>

57
00:03:34,881 --> 00:03:37,968
Let's see it! Let's see!
Ah, ah, ah!

58
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:40,429
[chuckles] Yeah, there it is!

59
00:03:40,929 --> 00:03:43,139
[clapping and cheering]

60
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:50,438
Well, we've waited so long
for the best of the best

