72
00:04:17,298 --> 00:04:19,634
<i>See you later, squids. </i>[bleep]

73
00:04:20,384 --> 00:04:24,180
[laughing] <i>What the </i>[bleep].
[laughs]<i> You can't say that on TV.</i>

74
00:04:26,057 --> 00:04:28,435
And this year's
<i>"Can You Stand the Heat"</i>

75
00:04:28,518 --> 00:04:31,103
celebrity champion is...

76
00:04:45,284 --> 00:04:47,495
Shane Roarke!

77
00:04:47,661 --> 00:04:49,790
- [clapping and cheering]
- [woman] Oh, my God!

78
00:04:50,247 --> 00:04:51,457
[Clara] Guys?

79
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:55,211
- Guys?
- [woman] Amazing!

80
00:04:56,086 --> 00:04:58,673
- Oh! He's so inspiring--
- Guys!

81
00:04:59,841 --> 00:05:01,050
If you're looking for something to do,

82
00:05:01,134 --> 00:05:03,220
maybe your jobs
could use a little attention?

83
00:05:04,221 --> 00:05:06,555
Yeah, I know,
but we have a really big day,

84
00:05:06,639 --> 00:05:08,641
so, we need to get going.

85
00:05:11,060 --> 00:05:13,521
Like now. Thank you.

86
00:05:15,273 --> 00:05:17,608
[indistinct chatter]

87
00:05:19,569 --> 00:05:23,447
Oh, Clara, you might as well
own this place.

88
00:05:23,531 --> 00:05:25,492
Oh, no, I am happy managing.

89
00:05:26,451 --> 00:05:28,119
Yeah, but your restaurant
in Chicago was great.

90
00:05:28,202 --> 00:05:30,997
I mean, I could just imagine
what you'd do to this place.

91
00:05:31,622 --> 00:05:35,252
Well, enough about that.
Let's just worry about these guests.

92
00:05:35,543 --> 00:05:37,336
Shane won!

93
00:05:37,629 --> 00:05:39,588
- Good for Shane.
- Everyone loves Shane.

94
00:05:40,923 --> 00:05:42,259
I have a table of seven coming in.

95
00:05:42,341 --> 00:05:43,759
- Can you please help me set up?
- OK.

96
00:05:44,009 --> 00:05:45,427
- Thank you.
- He's really cute, though.

97
00:05:45,512 --> 00:05:46,596
[Clara chuckles]

98
00:05:48,514 --> 00:05:49,891
[TV hostess]
<i>Remember that name, folks!</i>

99
00:05:49,975 --> 00:05:50,975
Shane Roarke!

100
00:05:51,225 --> 00:05:55,646
He's the country's most famous chef,
and most eligible bachelor.

101
00:05:56,105 --> 00:05:58,567
Breaking eggs...
And breaking hearts.

102
00:05:58,899 --> 00:06:00,276
Shane Roarke, everybody.

103
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:02,987
[audience cheering and clapping]

104
00:06:25,175 --> 00:06:26,845
[indistinct chatter]

105
00:06:36,855 --> 00:06:38,355
- Here we are.
- Thank you.

106
00:06:38,939 --> 00:06:39,858
Here we go.

107
00:06:40,108 --> 00:06:41,358
- Great. Thank you.
- [Clara] Enjoy.

108
00:06:41,817 --> 00:06:42,694
- Thanks.
- Hey,

109
00:06:42,776 --> 00:06:44,778
when you get a chance, could you run
some garlic bread to table three.

110
00:06:44,862 --> 00:06:46,740
- Absolutely. You're welcome.
- Thank you.

111
00:06:47,406 --> 00:06:49,533
Yeah, just go with the cab. Perfect.

112
00:06:50,909 --> 00:06:52,036
How is everything?

113
00:06:52,536 --> 00:06:54,288
Good. Your server
will be with you in just a minute.

114
00:06:54,538 --> 00:06:55,372
Thank you.

115
00:06:57,082 --> 00:06:58,584
How is everything over here?

116
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:03,255
Hey! [clapping]
We don't have all day here!

117
00:07:03,632 --> 00:07:05,050
I'll be right there, sir.

118
00:07:05,966 --> 00:07:07,636
- [Bonnie] I'm not 100 percent sure, but...
- What are you doing?

119
00:07:07,718 --> 00:07:09,220
[Bonnie] I think that guy wants you...

120
00:07:09,553 --> 00:07:10,387
You think?

121
00:07:10,639 --> 00:07:13,350
Hey, can I get two glasses
of red please? Thank you.

122
00:07:14,016 --> 00:07:15,143
[clapping]

123
00:07:15,476 --> 00:07:18,103
- Don't clap at the waitress. She's--
- I'm getting it done.

124
00:07:18,187 --> 00:07:20,564
- Shush. I got this one.
- Don't shush me!

125
00:07:22,024 --> 00:07:23,151
How can I help you?

126
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:28,531
[scoffs] I ordered a rare steak
and it's not bleeding.

127
00:07:28,615 --> 00:07:30,867
Well, you certainly seemed to have enjoyed
the first half of it.

128
00:07:31,283 --> 00:07:33,827
Yeah, but, I didn't love it.

129
00:07:34,329 --> 00:07:35,329
Shouldn't I love my steak...

130
00:07:37,122 --> 00:07:38,124
Clara?

131
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:43,295
Well, I'm afraid I can't guarantee you
love on this steak,

132
00:07:43,379 --> 00:07:46,632
but I can get you a new steak.
Rare, extra bloody.

133
00:07:47,591 --> 00:07:48,634
Touchdown!

134
00:07:49,259 --> 00:07:52,180
Oh, wow. Well, the date is over,

135
00:07:52,514 --> 00:07:56,225
and I am so sorry about... that.

136
00:07:56,308 --> 00:07:59,562
Um... [clears throat] Is there a taxi
stand outside? I'll just...

137
00:08:01,314 --> 00:08:03,065
I'll be back in just a minute.

138
00:08:05,901 --> 00:08:07,362
I bet you're glad to be back, huh?

139
00:08:07,946 --> 00:08:08,862
[Clara] Over the moon.

140
00:08:19,957 --> 00:08:22,502
Ah, I can't wait to get home.
I'm exhausted.

141
00:08:22,584 --> 00:08:25,045
I know. Me too. OK, but first
I gotta use the bathroom.

142
00:08:25,504 --> 00:08:28,173
- Again? You just went to the bathroom.
- Yeah, [scoffs] I gotta go again.

143
00:08:28,550 --> 00:08:29,843
- [phone ringing]
- Have you been stealing

144
00:08:29,968 --> 00:08:31,136
cheese from the kitchen again?

145
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:32,803
So?

146
00:08:33,138 --> 00:08:36,015
- [laughing] So, you're lactose intolerant.
- No, I'm not.

147
00:08:36,099 --> 00:08:37,267
Cheese just makes my stomach

148
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:39,269
- gurgle a little bit.
- [Clara] Right. My bad.

149
00:08:39,476 --> 00:08:41,980
- Enjoy your cheese. Yeah. Go.
- Can you hold my bag?

150
00:08:52,990 --> 00:08:55,826
Hi, how are you? I'm just checking in.

151
00:08:57,162 --> 00:08:58,495
- [thud]
- [Clara sighs]

152
00:09:04,793 --> 00:09:06,546
[Shane] Can I help you with this?

153
00:09:07,797 --> 00:09:09,758
- Oh, thank you.
- Oh, don't mention it.

154
00:09:09,798 --> 00:09:11,676
- [Clara] This isn't actually my cheese.
- Right.

155
00:09:11,759 --> 00:09:14,178
- Well, this is a nice piece of GruyÃ¨re.
- [Clara sighs]

156
00:09:14,386 --> 00:09:15,804
It's still not mine. It's... um...

157
00:09:16,181 --> 00:09:17,222
- [embarrassed laugh] It's not mine.
- [Shane] A friend's.

158
00:09:17,307 --> 00:09:18,182
Yeah.

159
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:20,894
- [Clara] Uh...
- [clears throat]

160
00:09:22,519 --> 00:09:23,812
[both sigh]

161
00:09:24,147 --> 00:09:27,609
Anyway, uh... enjoy your stay
at Thunder Mountain.

162
00:09:28,109 --> 00:09:29,318
Thank you, um...

163
00:09:29,778 --> 00:09:31,236
- [both] Clara.
- [Shane clears throat]

164
00:09:31,361 --> 00:09:33,615
Right. It's... on my necklace.

165
00:09:33,697 --> 00:09:34,657
[Shane] It is. Yeah.

166
00:09:36,826 --> 00:09:38,827
- Well, have a good night.
- You too. [chuckles]

167
00:09:39,913 --> 00:09:41,163
Bye. [laughs nervously]

168
00:09:48,962 --> 00:09:51,508
- Do you know who that is?
- Mm-hmm, yup, mm-hmm.

169
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:53,467
- [excited] It's Shane--
- Shh, shh, shh.

170
00:09:53,551 --> 00:09:55,677
- It's Shane Roarke!
- I know. I know.

171
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:57,263
You know, from that reality show earlier!

172
00:09:57,346 --> 00:09:59,389
- Yeah.
- He's standing-- [giggling] Here's here!

173
00:09:59,807 --> 00:10:01,934
Oh, he's even more handsome in real life.

174
00:10:02,393 --> 00:10:03,727
Did he make a pass at you?

175
00:10:05,230 --> 00:10:07,816
No, Bonnie, he handed me your cheese.

176
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:11,110
- [laughs]
- Come on.

177
00:10:13,238 --> 00:10:15,240
[inaudible]

178
00:10:16,908 --> 00:10:17,866
Great.

179
00:10:18,408 --> 00:10:20,327
[phone rings]

180
00:10:33,341 --> 00:10:34,716
[sighs]

181
