790
00:47:10,911 --> 00:47:12,121
Are you kidding?

791
00:47:12,913 --> 00:47:16,250
That guy microwaved his steak.

792
00:47:17,126 --> 00:47:18,085
Microwaved!

793
00:47:18,168 --> 00:47:19,878
- What!?
- It's blasphemy!

794
00:47:45,612 --> 00:47:46,572
So...

795
00:47:47,739 --> 00:47:49,157
what brought you here, anyway?

796
00:47:49,992 --> 00:47:52,702
I mean, it couldn't have just been
the job offer.

797
00:47:54,538 --> 00:47:56,581
No, you're right, it wasn't.

798
00:47:58,583 --> 00:48:02,463
When I finished the show,
I made myself a promise.

799
00:48:03,380 --> 00:48:04,255
Hmm.

800
00:48:04,465 --> 00:48:06,425
And being here is part of the promise?

801
00:48:06,925 --> 00:48:07,760
Mm-hmm.

802
00:48:08,552 --> 00:48:09,512
It is.

803
00:48:10,721 --> 00:48:12,431
And how long do you plan on staying?

804
00:48:13,724 --> 00:48:15,768
I mean, my contract's for six months.

805
00:48:16,434 --> 00:48:18,269
But I am...

806
00:48:19,146 --> 00:48:22,398
currently working on something
that might keep me here

807
00:48:23,108 --> 00:48:25,902
a little bit longer. Mm-hmm. Maybe.
- Oh?

808
00:48:26,737 --> 00:48:28,614
I still got to do
a little bit more research first.

809
00:48:28,697 --> 00:48:32,492
Mm. Well, aren't you mysterious?

810
00:48:32,742 --> 00:48:33,702
No.

811
00:48:36,996 --> 00:48:38,623
I want to know more about you.

812
00:48:39,125 --> 00:48:40,501
- Me.
- Mm-hmm.

813
00:48:41,418 --> 00:48:43,628
Well, I mean, you already know about me.

814
00:48:45,505 --> 00:48:48,384
I'm a recovering failure.

815
00:48:49,635 --> 00:48:51,427
Failing doesn't mean you're a failure.

816
00:48:52,972 --> 00:48:54,139
Unless you give up...

817
00:48:56,474 --> 00:48:57,934
I don't think that's you.

818
00:48:59,061 --> 00:48:59,936
Mm-mmm.

819
00:49:00,271 --> 00:49:01,396
- No?
- Mm-mmm.

820
00:49:02,981 --> 00:49:04,190
So, who am I?

821
00:49:05,775 --> 00:49:09,905
You are strong, determined.

822
00:49:12,115 --> 00:49:13,284
You're definitely smart.

823
00:49:14,617 --> 00:49:18,164
And you are... exceedingly beautiful.

824
00:49:18,539 --> 00:49:20,166
[both chuckle]

825
00:49:20,623 --> 00:49:23,626
Well, I mean,
feel free to go on. You're...

826
00:49:24,460 --> 00:49:26,422
- spot on so far.
- Am I?

827
00:49:28,047 --> 00:49:30,134
Oh, OK, all right. Um...

828
00:49:32,927 --> 00:49:34,471
you want a place of your own.

829
00:49:36,599 --> 00:49:39,893
You want to build it, and watch it grow.

830
00:49:40,643 --> 00:49:42,438
If I had to guess,

831
00:49:43,646 --> 00:49:45,440
I'd say that you are...

832
00:49:45,858 --> 00:49:47,775
planning on opening your own place again.

833
00:49:47,818 --> 00:49:49,360
- Hmm.
- Mm-hmm?

834
00:49:50,737 --> 00:49:53,282
Well, I mean, I've thought about it.

835
00:49:53,324 --> 00:49:54,407
Ah-ha.

836
00:49:57,952 --> 00:49:59,038
Whatever it is...

837
00:50:01,623 --> 00:50:02,583
you will do it.

838
00:50:04,376 --> 00:50:05,628
And it's going to be yours.

839
00:50:08,047 --> 00:50:09,005
And it's going to be great.

840
00:50:10,173 --> 00:50:11,300
[chuckles]

841
00:50:14,427 --> 00:50:16,347
Hey, you don't think it's gonna be
a problem with Mr. Peters

842
00:50:16,429 --> 00:50:17,847
if you keep coming over here, do you?

843
00:50:19,266 --> 00:50:20,643
Mr. Pete--
- Yeah.

844
00:50:20,726 --> 00:50:22,561
- Like me and Peters?
- You and Hugh, yeah.

845
00:50:24,313 --> 00:50:26,856
No, no, we're-- that's-- that's just...

846
00:50:27,065 --> 00:50:28,567
- It's business.
- Oh, is it?

847
00:50:28,650 --> 00:50:30,110
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Yeah? Yeah?

848
00:50:31,027 --> 00:50:32,612
Are you working on something big?

849
00:50:33,530 --> 00:50:36,742
Well, I mean, I promised
I wouldn't say anything.

850
00:50:36,909 --> 00:50:40,079
Ah, well, aren't you the mysterious one.

851
00:50:41,413 --> 00:50:42,539
Just a little.

852
00:50:50,047 --> 00:50:52,423
["Sounds Like Christmas"
by Keith Cooper playing]

853
00:52:21,347 --> 00:52:23,349
- Thank you.
- Here you go. Enjoy.

854
00:52:23,431 --> 00:52:24,349
Thank you.

855
00:52:26,559 --> 00:52:28,519
- You really like him, don't you?
- [Clara chuckles]

856
00:52:29,228 --> 00:52:30,938
I think I do. Yeah.

857
00:52:32,900 --> 00:52:36,195
OK. Well, when I first met Clive
I thought he was the most boring person

858
00:52:36,277 --> 00:52:37,237
in the entire world.

859
00:52:37,320 --> 00:52:39,405
You know, I almost didn't go
on a second date with him.

860
00:52:40,199 --> 00:52:42,034
But then I realized, after a while,

861
00:52:42,159 --> 00:52:43,994
he wasn't boring at all.
He was just shy.

862
00:52:45,536 --> 00:52:47,414
Of course, most city planners
are so boring.

863
00:52:47,831 --> 00:52:48,748
[Clara] No.

864
00:52:49,333 --> 00:52:51,585
- You don't say. [chuckles]
- [Bonnie] No, I--I do say.

865
00:52:52,378 --> 00:52:55,213
But the fact is, Clive is the--
He just is the funniest,

866
00:52:55,297 --> 00:52:57,215
most exciting city planner
I have ever met.

867
00:52:57,298 --> 00:53:00,260
And I feel really lucky
I gave him a chance.

868
00:53:00,802 --> 00:53:02,096
I really like Clive.

869
00:53:02,554 --> 00:53:03,472
Me too.

870
00:53:04,764 --> 00:53:06,599
No, I know
Shane isn't a city planner or anything.

871
00:53:07,059 --> 00:53:09,769
- But I guess famous chefs can be fun, too.
- [Clara chuckles]

872
00:53:11,313 --> 00:53:14,065
Yeah, I guess they can.

873
00:53:15,692 --> 00:53:18,528
Well, here's to chefs
and city planners.

874
00:53:23,032 --> 00:53:25,202
You know the craziest thing?
Guess what he [stutters] ordered?

875
00:53:26,536 --> 00:53:27,788
- What?
- Carrots.

876
00:53:27,954 --> 00:53:30,748
Really? I thought he was gonna order
some kind of deer.

877
00:53:31,333 --> 00:53:33,210
- I don't know...
- He would never!

878
00:53:33,710 --> 00:53:34,920
- Clara?
- Yeah.

879
00:53:35,003 --> 00:53:36,588
Can I see you in my office
for a minute, please?

880
00:53:36,672 --> 00:53:37,588
Oh, yeah, sure.

881
00:53:40,342 --> 00:53:43,387
Oh, oh. The principal's office.
Somebody's in trouble.

882
00:53:43,887 --> 00:53:45,097
Oh, you didn't hear?

883
00:53:45,681 --> 00:53:46,764
I am trouble.

884
00:53:48,391 --> 00:53:49,476
Yes, you are!

885
00:53:53,355 --> 00:53:54,231
Hey.

886
00:53:55,773 --> 00:53:57,693
Shut the door if you don't mind
and have a seat.

887
00:53:58,152 --> 00:53:59,277
[door closes]

888
00:54:03,157 --> 00:54:05,742
I see that you've been spending
a lot of time with Shane lately.

889
00:54:07,744 --> 00:54:10,289
Yes, my own personal time.

890
00:54:11,081 --> 00:54:12,081
Is that a problem?

891
00:54:12,458 --> 00:54:14,460
No, no, not per se.

892
00:54:14,543 --> 00:54:18,797
I just-- I wonder if you've had enough
free time to work on our little proposal.

893
00:54:19,172 --> 00:54:21,215
I mean, have you even spoken
to the Havens lately?

894
00:54:22,092 --> 00:54:25,344
Yes, actually! Um, I see them
almost every day at breakfast.

895
00:54:25,512 --> 00:54:28,514
Oh. OK. Um...

896
00:54:30,601 --> 00:54:33,603
You know, I--I, uh...
I got you something.

897
00:54:35,646 --> 00:54:38,150
What? What is this?

898
00:54:38,567 --> 00:54:40,027
It's just a little Christmas present.

899
00:54:40,485 --> 00:54:42,487
Oh, Hugh.

900
00:54:43,530 --> 00:54:45,032
I didn't get you anything.

901
00:54:45,407 --> 00:54:47,326
Don't be silly. Just--just open it.

902
00:54:51,914 --> 00:54:52,998
[Clara chuckles]

903
00:54:54,291 --> 00:54:56,460
Wow. This is beautiful.

904
00:54:58,753 --> 00:55:00,130
I don't know what to say.

905
00:55:01,965 --> 00:55:02,965
Thank you.

906
00:55:03,634 --> 00:55:05,010
You deserve it, Clara.

907
00:55:05,510 --> 00:55:07,221
I couldn't have done
any of this without you.

908
00:55:07,762 --> 00:55:10,097
And if this deal goes through,
you can buy jewelry yourself

909
00:55:10,181 --> 00:55:11,807
that'll make that look like a knock-off.

910
00:55:12,726 --> 00:55:16,438
But... if you could encourage them,

911
00:55:17,146 --> 00:55:18,773
maybe speed things up.

912
00:55:18,856 --> 00:55:21,108
I'd love to get the deal done
before the year end.

913
00:55:21,860 --> 00:55:23,152
Before New Yearâs?

914
00:55:25,112 --> 00:55:26,239
Um...

915
00:55:27,907 --> 00:55:31,286
Uh, I think they were kind of hoping
for a bit of time with this.

916
00:55:32,204 --> 00:55:34,206
Ah.

917
00:55:35,206 --> 00:55:37,960
All right. This, um,
this was supposed to be a surprise,

918
00:55:38,043 --> 00:55:41,380
but I was hoping to close the deal
sooner because...

919
00:55:42,297 --> 00:55:45,050
I have a project that I want
to send you to New York for.

920
00:55:46,425 --> 00:55:47,302
New York?

921
00:55:48,219 --> 00:55:50,681
Like you want me to oversee
another acquisition or...

922
00:55:50,806 --> 00:55:53,559
Actually, I want to invest
in a new restaurant.

923
00:55:54,434 --> 00:55:56,186
It would be yours. Ours.

924
00:55:57,061 --> 00:55:58,855
But because I'm here
doing the Haven deal,

925
00:55:59,438 --> 00:56:00,440
if we speed it up,

926
00:56:00,523 --> 00:56:02,943
that would open up
the New York opportunity for you.

927
00:56:04,152 --> 00:56:06,530
Yeah! Wow!

928
00:56:07,989 --> 00:56:08,907
It's great.

929
00:56:12,369 --> 00:56:14,621
You know what? Leave it to me.

930
00:56:15,121 --> 00:56:18,458
They trust me and I think I can help
speed them along.

931
00:56:19,376 --> 00:56:21,545
- I know you can.
- You can count on me.

932
00:56:22,378 --> 00:56:25,257
Good. Uh, so?

933
00:56:26,925 --> 00:56:28,260
Yeah, uh, the schedule.

934
00:56:28,342 --> 00:56:32,472
It's just Bonnie's Thursday,
we need to switch it...

935
00:56:46,235 --> 00:56:48,739
- Oh, hi, there!
- Hi. Here.

936
00:56:48,822 --> 00:56:50,239
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

937
00:56:55,494 --> 00:56:57,956
So, I've been meaning to ask.

938
00:56:58,039 --> 00:57:00,250
Um... what are you doing
for Christmas?

939
00:57:01,418 --> 00:57:02,793
I don't know. I haven't, uh,

940
00:57:03,378 --> 00:57:05,672
I haven't really thought about it.
I might--I might go back to the city.

941
00:57:06,465 --> 00:57:07,548
Hmm.

942
00:57:08,215 --> 00:57:09,175
Hmm-hmm.

943
00:57:10,135 --> 00:57:11,010
Well, that makes sense.

944
00:57:11,094 --> 00:57:13,221
I'm sure you probably want
to see your family.

945
00:57:13,304 --> 00:57:14,764
[both chuckle]

946
00:57:15,849 --> 00:57:17,893
Have you told me about your family yet?

947
00:57:19,393 --> 00:57:21,021
You know, I don't think I have.

948
00:57:22,648 --> 00:57:26,193
- Do you have brothers or sisters?
- No. No, just me.

949
00:57:26,818 --> 00:57:28,362
